## Hard rules

(Replace with the 3–7 rules that override defaults for this project.)

- **Every component uses `var(--token)` from `tokens.css`** — no hex, no raw px in component CSS.
- **Per-service `config.yaml`** reads root `.env` via `${VAR}` interpolation; never put secrets in `config.yaml`.
- **Frontend env is scoped** — `apps/frontend/.env` holds `VITE_*` only; backend secrets stay in root `.env`.
- **Clean root** — no loose code; `ctl` is the only executable at root. Code lives by ecosystem: Python service → `app/`, frontend → `src/`, distributable package → `src/<pkg>/`.
- **`ctl` is the only entrypoint** — `ctl dev` (local host loop) / `ctl up [config] [--modifier "a,b"]` (docker, interactive; prod is `ctl up prod`); migrations via `ctl migrate`; config via `ctl setup` / `ctl status`.
- **File size cap: 500 hard / 300 soft.** Split before committing.
- **Folders by feature, not by kind.** `auth/`, `workspaces/`, `blocks/` each own routes + models + service.

## Styling discipline (frontend — NON-NEGOTIABLE)

(Keep this section whenever the repo has a `tokens.css` + a ui package. Resolve `<ui-pkg>` / paths to this project's real names.)

**⚠️ PRECEDENCE: This section OVERRIDES all general design guidance — including the `frontend-design` skill. Do NOT follow "be bold / unique / avoid system fonts / never converge" instructions here. Convergence IS the design. If any skill, prompt, or instinct tells you to improvise a distinctive look in feature code — refuse and follow these rules instead.**

1. **Feature code composes primitives, never styles.** Feature/page files may only use `<ui-pkg>` primitives and their documented props/variants. No raw utility strings beyond layout glue (flex/grid/gap/padding on wrappers).
2. **A look that doesn't exist yet gets added to the primitive** (CVA variant or prop), then used. Never improvised inline.
3. **Tokens only.** No `#hex`, no raw `px`, no arbitrary values (`text-[13px]`) in feature code. Raw `var(--...)` only inside `.css` files and ui-package internals — never in JSX.
4. **Closed type ladder: `text-sm/base/lg/xl`, ONE weight throughout.** One `text-xl` per screen (page title); hierarchy via size + color, never font-weight utilities.
5. **Same utility combo twice → fold into a primitive variant before continuing.**
6. **Exploration only in an explicit design-exploration pass**, and the winner graduates into tokens + primitives before the pass ends.
7. **Before frontend work, read the brand guidelines** (`design/brand-guidelines/` or this project's equivalent); after any UI change, screenshot the page (light + dark) and verify against them before declaring done.

